Afrikan-Centred Historian, Social Scientist Thando Sipuye says racism is still deeply entrenched and memorialised in most, if not all, former colonial towns and cities of South Africa. Sipuye made these comments after his visit to the Karoo Town of Graaff-Reinet in the Eastern Cape for the burial of Robert Mangaliso Sobukwe’s son Dinilesizwe Sobukwe a few weeks ago. Sipuye and journalist and author Lukhanyo Calata spoke to Morning Live about the structures that still exist in  small towns and how they affect  communities. WATCH FULL INTERVIEW 